import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['actual'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Actual Temperature')
    plt.axvline(data['actual'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['actual'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Actual Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of actual temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], label='Actual Temperature', color='blue')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['normal'], label='Normal Temperature', color='orange')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('How does the actual temperature compare to the normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.xlabel('Forecasted Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecasted temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    
    plt.scatter(data['actual'], data['forecast'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Actual Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Forecasted Temperature')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between actual temperature and forecasted temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Actual vs Forecast'], loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    data['day'] = data['day'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['record'])]
    data['record'] = data['record'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    
    grouped_data = data.groupby('day')['record'].count()
    
    plt.bar(grouped_data.index, grouped_data.values)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Temperature Records')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature records by day?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
